Git -> version control system
    a) track the history
    b) collaborate

GitHub -> Platform to store your code
    a) add
    b) commit

# for Git
>> vs code
>> Git bash

~ -> root directory

git config --global user.name "My name"
git config --global user.email "email"
git config --list

# basic commands

clone:
    a) remote -> GitHub
    b) local -> laptop
    command: 
        git clone <-repository link->
        cd <-directory name-> #to get inside and directory
        cd .. #to go back to previous directory
        cd ~ #to go to root directory
        ls #to check files
        ls -a #to get all the hidden files 
        ls -force #for powershell to get all hidden files

Status:
    command:
        git status
    #types of files
        a) untracked files -> new files
        b) modified files -> changes made but not yet staged
        c) staged files -> changes ready to be committed
        d) unmodified files -> no changes

add:
    command:
        git add <-file name->
        to add all files: git add .

commit:
    command:
        git commit -m "message"

push:
    command:
        git push origin <-branch name-> 
        or
        git push origin main

pull:
    command:
        git pull origin <-branch name->
        or 
        git pull origin main

 init: # to initialize a new git repository
    command:
        git init # to create a new repository locally
        mkdir <-directory name-> # to create a new directory
        cd <-directory name->
        #go to GitHub to create a new repository
        git remote add origin <-repository link-> # to link local repo to remote repo
        git remote -v # to verify the link
        git branch # to check current branch
        git branch -M main # to rename current branch to main
        git push- # to push the code to remote repo for the first time

General steps:
    1) to clone and work
        create repo
        clone it
        make changes
        add
        commit
        push

    2) to create a new repo and push code
        create repo
        git init
        git remote add origin <-repository link->
        git branch -M main
        git add .
        git commit -m "message"
        git push -u origin main

--- Git Branches ---

    command:
        Creating Branches:
            git branch # to view all branches
            git branch -M <-new-branch-name-> # to rename current branch
            git checkout <-branch-name-> # to switch to another branch
            git checkout -b <-new-branch-name-> # to create and switch to new branch
            git branch -d <-branch-name-> # to delete a branch
        
        Merging Branches:
            a) using Git
                git diff <-branch1-> <-branch2-> # to see the differences between two branches
                git merge <-branch-to-merge-> # merge the specified branch into the current branch

            b) using Pull Request on GitHub
                create a pull request

---Merge Conflict---
    # when the same part of the same file is modified in both branches
    # need to resolve manually
    # after resolving, add, commit and push

--- Undoing Changes ---
    command:
        git reset <-file-name-> # unstage a file
        git reset # to unstage all files
        git reset HEAD~1 # to undo the last commit but keep changes in working directory
        git reset <-commit-hash-> --hard # to undo commits and discard changes
        git log # to view commit history

---Fork---
    # to create a copy of someone else's repository to your GitHub account
    # make changes in the forked repo
    # create a pull request to the original repo to suggest changes
